<h1 class="hero-h">ChatGPT for Nonprofit Leaders: <em>what actually works in 2026.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">OpenAI's ChatGPT is OpenAI's flagship product with multimodal capabilities and the GPT Store ecosystem. For nonprofit leaders, it's most valuable for donor communications, grant writing, program promotion, board reporting. This is the practical playbook — specific use cases, prompts that work, and what to avoid.</p>
<div class="verdict"><div class="verdict-l">The short version</div><p class="verdict-p">Nonprofit Leaders should use ChatGPT for donor communications, grant writing, program promotion, board reporting. Plus daily-driver use cases: volunteer recruitment, annual report production. Cost: $20 (Plus) or $30/seat (Team). Pair with workflow-specific tools for production deployment. Most nonprofit leaders see 3-5× productivity lift on the right tasks.</p></div>
</div></div>

<div style="background:#0A1A0A;border-top:1px solid #1A3A1A;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.25rem 2.5rem;">
